till further orders.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/coronavirus-updates-live-total-number-of-coronavirus-cases-in-india-maharashtra-telangana-haryana/liveblog/74632927.cms|title=Coronavirus outbreak live updates: Mumbai cops invoke section 144 to ban group tours till March 31|date=15 March 2020|work=Times of India|access-date=15 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Gujarat]] government announced that all schools, colleges, cinema halls will be closed till 31 March, however the board examinations will be conducted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india/breaking-coronavirus-gujarat-shuts-schools-colleges-covid19-598370|title=Coronavirus: Gujarat shuts all schools, colleges, cinema halls from tomorrow|last=Hardaha|first=Rashi|date=15 March 2020|website=www.indiatvnews.com|language=en|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref> [[Bihar Public Service Commission]] (BPSC) has postponed all the recruitment exams till 31 March.<ref>{{cite web |title=BPSC assistant engineer main exam 2019 postponed amid coronavirus outbreak| url=https://m.hindustantimes.com/education/bpsc-assistant-engineer-main-exam-2019-postponed-amid-coronavirus-outbreak/story-rQzUCoRWC4NHWa7Gq0SQTN.html|website=Hindustan times|author=| date=14 March 2020}}</ref> [[Vaishno Devi]] Shrine Board issued an advisory asking non-resident Indians and foreigners not to visit the temple for 28 days after landing in India.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/coronavirus-cases-in-india-live-news-latest-updates-march15/liveblog/74633220.cms|title=Coronavirus News Live Updates: Third case reported in Telangana|date=15 March 2020|work=Economic Times|access-date=15 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Tamil Nadu]] and [[Telangana]] governments declared closure of schools, malls and theatres till 31 March.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Narasimhan|first=T. E.|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/current-